http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation_(website)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SKEMA Business Schoolprovides funding as a member of The Conversation FR.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.262648767607683e-25, \"text\": \"The Conversation\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\"}, {\"begin\": 527, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6847175274209231, \"rank\": 0.4604562610901123, \"text\": \"FR\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners  https://doi.org/10.64628/AB.tm5yej64x  Share article  Print article  Since the Olympic Games in Paris began, the French president, Emmanuel Macron, hasposted the statement\\\"This is France!\\\"\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 664, \"end\": 680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 682, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"several times on his social media platforms.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Macron has been implicitly asserting that he is delivering on hispersonal visionof the event, and of France.\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.084438925797501e-35, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since his election in 2017, he has sought to project a diverse, cosmopolitan and outward-facing France while at the same time strengthening existing preconceptions of its style, culture and history.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony was therefore theembodiment of Macron's ambitions.\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1147, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.084438925797501e-35, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It combined landmarks like the Eiffel Tower and key figures from French history, such as Marie Antoinette, with cultural, musical and fashion representations of modern France.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.532486303755351e-34, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These included surfers, rappers and members of LGBTQ+ communities.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, as recent events in French domestic politics have demonstrated, many among the country's population do not like their president's vision.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7430799275188197, \"rank\": 0.2920235655456488, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those from the extreme left balk at what they see as Macron's globalist tendencies, which the International Olympic Committee (IOC) issharing and accentuatingby staging the Games.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.084438925797501e-35, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, those from the extreme right have longresented and resistedMacron's Parisian-centric and urban-led vision of diversity and modernity.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1885, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was evident in reactions to the opening ceremony's depiction of Leonardo da Vinci's painting, The Last Supper, in which drag queens, a transgender model and a naked singer appeared.\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9405919535112806e-17, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's Catholic churchcondemnedthe sketch as a \\\"mockery of Christianity\\\".\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2073, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2082, \"end\": 2090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.999999999447482, \"rank\": 5.299521943908142e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 2134, \"end\": 2146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998884436598, \"rank\": 1.1116583679763219e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympic organisers have sinceissued an apology, though this is unlikely to have placated Muslim communities around the world.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2245, \"end\": 2251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9999067747978104, \"rank\": 9.323268273294547e-05, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some among themlabelledparts of the opening ceremony \\\"absurd\\\", \\\"disgusting\\\" and a \\\"promotion of satanic forms\\\".\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Others saw it as an attempt by the west toimpose its valueson them.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This sentiment was apparently shared by the Chinese state broadcaster, China Central Television, whoseevent commentators went quietduring the segments in which members of LGBTQ+ communities appeared.\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2507, \"end\": 2514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7956961145583261, \"rank\": 0.24720022748351358, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2534, \"end\": 2558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"China Central Television\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China has a record ofseeking to suppressthese communities.\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2663, \"end\": 2668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999978923137154, \"rank\": 1.8595750347499792e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For some French Muslims, there may also have been dismay at the depiction of a religious scene at an event being staged by a French state entity.\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2732, \"end\": 2746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.553342011901041e-21, \"text\": \"French Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2732, \"end\": 2746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.553342011901041e-21, \"text\": \"French Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2848, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7430799275188197, \"rank\": 0.2920235655456488, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, it wasannouncedlate last year that Muslim women would not be allowed to wear their hijabs when competing for France at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2915, \"end\": 2921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9999067747978104, \"rank\": 9.323268273294547e-05, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}, {\"begin\": 2989, \"end\": 2995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The justification for this decision was that it would breach the country's secularist principles, which create a clear separation between religion and state.\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That decision came at an especially sensitive time, following the Hamas-led October 7 attacks and Macron's invitation to France's chief Rabbi tolight Hannukah candlesat the \\u00c9lys\\u00e9e Palace.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.084438925797501e-35, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3293, \"end\": 3299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanukkah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hannukah\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanukkah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanukkah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The war in Gaza continues to cast a shadow over the Games.\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3371, \"end\": 3375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999951625730907, \"rank\": 4.837450533343564e-06, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, there are rumours of some athletes beingprepared to withdrawfrom the event if they are required to compete directly against an Israeli athlete.\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3554, \"end\": 3561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999976716389759, \"rank\": 2.305831999748382e-06, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The simmering threat of such direct action has already manifested itself at the Games.\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During a football match between Mali and Israel on July 24, members of the crowd unfurled banners condemning the latter country and waved flags insupport of Palestine.\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3691, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9633799349531402, \"rank\": 0.038012069386655925, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}, {\"begin\": 3700, \"end\": 3706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.381943647754403e-16, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 3816, \"end\": 3825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.9350872574146837, \"rank\": 0.06941475031613571, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The vast majority (95%) of Malians are Muslim, andthere are 120,000 peoplefrom Mali living in France.\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 3928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3854, \"end\": 3861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Mali\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1103235730797818e-19, \"text\": \"Malians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demographics_of_Mali\"}, {\"begin\": 3906, \"end\": 3910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9633799349531402, \"rank\": 0.038012069386655925, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}, {\"begin\": 3921, \"end\": 3927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Israel is not the only country where there is some disquiet.\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3930, \"end\": 3936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.381943647754403e-16, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following recentdoping scandalsand the invasion of Ukraine, most Russian and Belarusian athletes are banned from participating in Paris.\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 4127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4042, \"end\": 4049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999985620889, \"rank\": 1.4285872879034597e-09, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 4056, \"end\": 4063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.8411553788864277, \"rank\": 0.18764606571592873, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4068, \"end\": 4078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9999972428956235, \"rank\": 2.754565979109586e-06, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}, {\"begin\": 4121, \"end\": 4126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few athletes are competing as neutrals, but national flags, anthems and other national symbols are banned, and no government or state officials have been invited.\", \"from\": 4128, \"to\": 4292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The exclusion of Russia has led to speculation that its agents may have been responsible for a series ofrailway sabotagesthat caused significant travel disruption on the opening day of the Games.\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4311, \"end\": 4317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though nobody was hurt or killed, such attacks undermine public confidence, impose economic and social costs on people, and were clearly an attempt to tarnish the image of France.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4662, \"end\": 4668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France has a long-held reputation for successfully delivering numerous major events each year.\", \"from\": 4671, \"to\": 4765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4671, \"end\": 4677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there was alsodisruptionat the Uefa Champions League final in 2022, which was being staged at the Stade de France (the main Olympic venue this summer).\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Liverpool supporters were put through a traumatising experience when entering the stadium, and riot police teargassed spectators while failing to protect them from being attacked by local thugs.\", \"from\": 4927, \"to\": 5126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4932, \"end\": 4941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9940085230301458, \"rank\": 0.006027590277187619, \"text\": \"Liverpool\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liverpool_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This followed Paris quickly stepping in to stage the match after Uefa removed St Petersburg'sright to host the gamefollowing Russia's invasion of Ukraine.\", \"from\": 5128, \"to\": 5282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5142, \"end\": 5147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5253, \"end\": 5259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5274, \"end\": 5281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999985620889, \"rank\": 1.4285872879034597e-09, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether these events were another deliberate attempt to diminish France or just a coincidence remains debatable.\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5348, \"end\": 5354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9860950365109685, \"rank\": 0.012043315481778536, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some have suggested that Russia's president, Vladimir Putin, has wanted toundermine the IOCfor much of the past decade.\", \"from\": 5397, \"to\": 5516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5422, \"end\": 5428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5442, \"end\": 5456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0415954126373348e-31, \"text\": \"Vladimir Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He sees it as a western institution governed by values and rules that maintain a dominance he resents.\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, Russia has been planning to host the World Friendship Games a little more than a month after the Paris Olympics finishes.\", \"from\": 5621, \"to\": 5751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5630, \"end\": 5636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999989175922965, \"rank\": 1.0822869352656358e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While there is some confusion over whether the event will bepostponed to 2025, there are claims that more than 100 nations have already committed to participating in what may ultimately come to pose an existential threat to the modern Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 6004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC normally does its utmost to control the places and spaces that it selects to host Olympic events, whether that means suppressing displays of activism, preventing acts of terrorism, or even minimising the commercial intrusion of brands that have no legal right to associate with the event.\", \"from\": 6006, \"to\": 6302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6010, \"end\": 6013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1630988473845512e-31, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, such is the currently fractious nature of local and global geopolitics that we should expect more controversy before the Olympic flame in Paris is finally extinguished.\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6451, \"end\": 6456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.477388917670513e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6483, \"to\": 6537, \"entities\": []}]}"